"{\"abstract\":\"Frank-Wolfe methods (FW) have gained significant interest in the machine learning community due to their ability to efficiently solve large problems that admit a sparse structure (e.g. sparse vectors and low-rank matrices). However the performance of the existing FW method hinges on the quality of the linear approximation. This typically restricts FW to smooth functions for which the approximation quality, indicated by a global curvature measure, is reasonably good. In this paper, we propose a modified FW algorithm amenable to nonsmooth functions, subject to a separability assumption, by optimizing for approximation quality over all affine functions, given a neighborhood of interest. We analyze theoretical properties of the proposed algorithm and demonstrate that it overcomes many issues associated with existing methods in the context of nonsmooth low-rank matrix estimation.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"144789120\",\"name\":\"E. Cheung\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/144789120\"},{\"authorId\":\"48513508\",\"name\":\"Y. Li\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/48513508\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2006.07562\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"36919708\",\"name\":\"Mohammadi Zaki\"},{\"authorId\":\"1749795318\",\"name\":\"Avi Mohan\"},{\"authorId\":\"2226401\",\"name\":\"A. Gopalan\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"b3528a18e39677457ec5de67add95fcc17857680\",\"title\":\"Explicit Best Arm Identification in Linear Bandits Using No-Regret Learners\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/b3528a18e39677457ec5de67add95fcc17857680\",\"venue\":\"ArXiv\",\"year\":2020}],\"corpusId\":51605391,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2018/281\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Mathematics\",\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"ef7f3a83744ab2636d7b6bf3f2be34de02b35eb7\",\"references\":[{\